{
  "stem": "1415.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Now that was a-- a story in itself, because [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] my-- they were telling people that they're going-- they're forming a Jewish state someplace in Madagascar or in Timbuktu, whatever they-- they told us.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And my brother came, and he loaded us onto a wagon.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And we were sitting on the wagon to go on, and by miracle, the last minute, he changed his mind and took us all off and smuggled us into the ghetto, which was a smaller ghetto which was right across the street from where-- where those wagons were loaded.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "I mean, just a half-- half a street to cross, like from one side of the street to the other, and we were already in the middle.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And somehow he smuggled me into the ghetto, because it was not as hard for-- for adults to be going in, but for children-- and I think I was about seven at the time-- it was very difficult.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Well, he got me into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And for a while there, I I don't know if they knew what to do with me, the truth.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And afterwards, people were rounded up to go to work, so he had to hide me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And I was hidden in a-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in an attic where he lived, where my brother lived.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "My family was separated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "My-- my mother and father were someplace else.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "I don't even know where they were at the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "But I was up in the attic, and my brother was with a lot of younger people, maybe policemen like him or-- he-- he wasn't with my parents.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "He wasn't with my-- with anybody.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "I don't even know where my little brother was.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
